# Self-Service Business Dashboards

This Notebook provides access to Business Grade Dashboards and tile/variable examples. Scroll down for a detailed description of the Dashboard, Use Cases, Install Instructions and much more. You can download/upload any content and use the dashboard as is. Or you can take certain portions of the dashboard, remove/add content to fit your specific use case. If you are interested in building your own content from scratch within your wireframe, listed below are a few tile and variable examples to get you started.

## Code Tile Examples

- [Single Value](https://github.com/dynatrace-perfclinics/community-tips-tricks/tree/main/ep19/SingleValue.json) 
- [Table](https://github.com/dynatrace-perfclinics/community-tips-tricks/tree/main/ep19/Table.json) 
- [Categorical Bar Chart](https://github.com/dynatrace-perfclinics/community-tips-tricks/tree/main/ep19/CBC.json) 
- [Timeseries Chart](https://github.com/dynatrace-perfclinics/community-tips-tricks/tree/main/ep19/TSC.json) 
- [Pie Chart](https://github.com/dynatrace-perfclinics/community-tips-tricks/tree/main/ep19/PC.json)

## Code Variable Examples

- [Applications](https://github.com/dynatrace-perfclinics/community-tips-tricks/tree/main/ep19/Apps.json) 
- [FrictionKPI](https://github.com/dynatrace-perfclinics/community-tips-tricks/tree/main/ep19/FrictionVariable.json) 

## Executive Overview Dashboard
This dashboard provides an executive level overview on KPIs and Customer Experience.
 
![](data:image/webp;base64,)

### Prerequisites

Required: [Create a conversion goal](https://www.dynatrace.com/support/help/platform-modules/digital-experience/web-applications/analyze-and-use/define-conversion-goals) for a user action that indicates the start of a business transaction (i.e. Login Page).

Required: [Create a conversion goal](https://www.dynatrace.com/support/help/platform-modules/digital-experience/web-applications/analyze-and-use/define-conversion-goals) for a user action that indicates a completed business transaction (i.e. Order Confirmation Page).

### Target Audience

- Application Owner
- Line of Business
- Executive

### Use Cases

- Are performance issues impacting my customer experience?
- Are errors impacting my customer experience?
- Are performance and error trends impacting my customer experience?
- Are my KPIs trending in the right direction?
- What days/times do I have good customer experience?
- Are my users converting efficiently? 
- Does a change in my APDEX score impact my customer experience?
- Are my users staying engaged?
- Do I have user satisfaction problems/trends?
- Is my traffic trending in the right direction?
- Is my bounce rate normal and trending in the right direction?

### Install Instructions

- Click [Dashboard JSON](https://github.com/dynatrace-perfclinics/community-tips-tricks/tree/main/ep19/Executive%20Overview.json) and select Download raw file ![](data:image/webp;base64,)
- Launch the Dashboard app
- Select Upload and select the JSON file for your download folder
- Select Review all code in the upper right hand corner of your Dashboard
- Check Always trust code in this document and then select Accept and run
- Test out you Dashboard by selecting options from the Variable dropdown list and adjusting the Dashboard timeframe

## Revenue Overview Dashboard

## Performance Conversion Analysis (Application) Dashboard

This dashboard provides a performance conversion analysis for your applications and tells you if the performance for any User Action impacts your conversion rate.

![](data:image/webp;base64,)

### Prerequisites

Required: [Create a conversion goal](https://www.dynatrace.com/support/help/platform-modules/digital-experience/web-applications/analyze-and-use/define-conversion-goals) for a user action that indicates a completed business transaction (i.e. Order Confirmation Page).

Required: [Create a session property](https://www.dynatrace.com/support/help/platform-modules/digital-experience/custom-applications/additional-configuration/define-custom-action-and-session-properties) from your conversion page (i.e. String: OrderCompleted).

### Target Audience

- Application Owner
- Line of Business
- Executive
- Web Developer

### Use Cases

-	Do I have a problem with my website?
-	Is this problem impacting my users?
-	What KPI is causing the problem?
-	What user action(s) do I need to tune?
-	How much improvement do I need to achieve to maximize conversions?
-	How much is this problem costing my business?

### Install Instructions

- Click [Dashboard JSON](https://github.com/dynatrace-perfclinics/community-tips-tricks/tree/main/ep19/Performance%20Conversion%20Analysis%20(Application).json) and select Download raw file ![](data:image/webp;base64,)
- Launch the Dashboard app
- Select Upload and select the JSON file for your download folder
- Select Review all code in the upper right hand corner of your Dashboard
- Check Always trust code in this document and then select Accept and run
- Test out you Dashboard by selecting options from the Variable dropdown list and adjusting the Dashboard timeframe

## Performance Conversion Analysis (KUA) Dashboard
This dashboard provides a performance conversion analysis for your applications and tells you if the performance for a certain User Action impacts your conversion rate.

![](data:image/webp;base64,)

### Prerequisites

Required: [Create a conversion goal](https://www.dynatrace.com/support/help/platform-modules/digital-experience/web-applications/analyze-and-use/define-conversion-goals) for a user action that indicates a completed business transaction (i.e. Order Confirmation Page).

Required: [Create a session property](https://www.dynatrace.com/support/help/platform-modules/digital-experience/custom-applications/additional-configuration/define-custom-action-and-session-properties) from your conversion page (i.e. String: OrderCompleted).

### Target Audience

- Application Owner
- Line of Business
- Executive
- Web Developer

### Use Cases

- What is the APDEX for my Key User Action?
- Is my user traffic increasing?
- Does the performance of my Key User Action impacting my Conversion Rate?
- Are users that interact with my Key User Action converting efficiently?
- What is the optimal performance for my Key User Action with respect to conversions?
- How much improvement do I need to achieve to maximize conversions?
- How much is this problem costing my business?
